cse:attribute.name: og:description
cse:attribute.value: By Kathy Novak So much of this past week has been consumed with getting into Tacloban. The airport was badly damaged, and flights limited; ferries from Cebu to Leyte Province were dependent on good weather to cross; then from the port at Ormoc to Tacloban, it was a journey across a road littered with debris and plagued with security concerns.
